    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>December 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1859</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I beg leave to acknowledge the safe receipt of, &amp; thank you for, your Bill for £180, due May 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1860.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Pray believe me | My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | Charles Darwin To | John Murray Esq<hi rend="superscript">e</hi></p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Murray’s accounts indicate that this was the sum that CD received as his share of the profits on the first edition of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref> (Peckham ed. 1959, p. 775). The sum is recorded in CD’s Account book (Down House MS) under the date of 28 May 1860.</note>
        </div>        
            
